  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Deseed the<strong> pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and roughly chop into bite-size pieces</p><p>Crush the <strong>garlic clove<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and remove the skin</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614002912948-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614002912948-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614002912948-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614002912948-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614002912948-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> pieces of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of an A3 sheet of paper and layer them over each other</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to the middle with the <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Make 2 separate parcels!</p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the pepper to form 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> sealed parcel<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and add to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the pepper has softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614002927370-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
