            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash, then chop the <strong>cavolo nero</strong> roughly, removing any tough stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped cavolo nero</strong> to the reserved pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a splash of <strong>water</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until wilted</p><p>Squeeze the <strong>remaining lemon juice</strong> into the<strong> cooked bulgur wheat </strong>and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>lemony bulgur wheat</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1614003214475-x200.jpg",
